        <p>The <strong>Windows Template Library</strong> (<strong>WTL</strong>) is a free software, object-oriented {'C++'|link_urls:'/l'} template library for <strong>Win32</strong> development.</p>
        <p>WTL was created by {'Microsoft'|link_urls:'/c'} employee <strong>Nenad Stefanovic</strong> for internal use and later released as an unsupported add-on to {'Visual Studio'|link_urls:'i'} and the Win32 Framework SDK.</p>
        <p>It was developed primarily as a light-weight alternative to the <strong>Microsoft Foundation Classes</strong> {'MFC'|link_urls:'i'} and builds upon Microsoft's ATL, another lightweight API widely used to create COM and {'ActiveX'|link_urls:'i'} libraries.</p>
